  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIt was noticed sometimes in chats there are missing messages after offline history fetched when using Mobile network.\r\nThere are no certain steps to reproduce the exact issue however, reproduction below may show very similar steps which can reveal the root cause of issue maybe. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAll messages received when open chat under mobile network\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n<img width=\"522\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-09-09 at 16 00 27\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/132691293-1b302226-7508-4e3e-b105-3f2a691d0c31.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n1) Enable Mobile network on your device \r\n2) Open Status\r\n3) Create new account\r\n4) When on Chats view there is a crossed out mobile icon indicating 'Offline history won't be fetched'\r\n5) Join any public chat with messages (e.g. `status-desktop`)\r\n6) Tap 'Fetch more messages' - it will fetch the day before yesterdays messages \r\n7) Close Status (or log-out of account)\r\n8) Enable WiFi\r\n9) Login to account and open the chat you joined to (messages from the last 24h should be fetched and \"join\" the history you've fetched in 6th step above\r\n10) Check whether there are missed messages in the message history\r\n\r\n **NOTE** If you reopen an app then it's very likely all the history is fetched and all messages are visible as expected, - but above steps may reveal where is the _\"I have missing messages\"_ problem exists\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n",
